      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The inflammation disappearing only means the bacteria are *weakened*, not necessarily *dead*. Stopping early is a prime way to select for the hardiest, most resistant strains, which is a major public health issue. To truly clear the infection, you need to maintain the antibiotic concentration in your system long enough to kill every single microscopic survivor. Stick to the full 10 days, or better yet, double-check with your prescribing doctor to confirm the full course is necessary for your specific infection.",
      "source": "target",
